== Miso-Sesame Sauce ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @sesame dressing{1.5%oz}, @sweet Thai
chili sauce{1%oz}, @miso sauce concentrate{2}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @soy sauce{2%tsp},
@rice wine vinegar{1/4%tsp}, and as many @Korean chili flakes{1%tsp} as you
like (we used half).

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and
toast, stirring frequently, until fragrant and golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer to bowl with miso-sesame sauce.

== Stir-Fried Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz} and @edamame{4%oz}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}.

== Noodles ==

Bring a #large pot{} of water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Once water is boiling, gently separate @Sun Noodle fresh noodles{10%oz} and
add to pot. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse thoroughly under cold water, at least ~{30%seconds}. Shake off
any excess water.

== Assembly ==

Transfer drained noodles to bowl with sauce. Using #tongs{}, toss until noodles
are evenly coated.

Add half the scallions and half the stir-fried veggies; toss until evenly
combined.

Divide noodles between bowls; top with remaining stir-fried veggies. Garnish
with remaining scallions and serve.